l humanism in favor of more robust, capacious, and worldly senses of the human and the humanities. Chuh presents the aesthetics of illiberal humanism as vital to the creation of sensibilities and worlds capable of making life and lives flourish.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Sep 2020) 0aAestheticsxPolitical aspects. 0aAmerican literaturexPolitical aspects. 0aArt, Moderny21st centuryxPolitical aspectszUnited States. 0aEurocentrism. 0aHumanismxStudy and teaching (Higher). 0aLiteraturexStudy and teaching (Higher). 0aPolitics and culture. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Semiotics & Theory.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK eBook-Package 2019z978311069632540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478002383zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478002383423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781478002383.jpg  a978-3-11-069632-5  DUK eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles